# ALIEN on AMD GPUs
Porting an artificial life simulator from CUDA to ROCm/HIP
Summary: How I ported ALIEN, a particle-physics artificial life simulator, from CUDA to ROCm/HIP so it runs on AMD GPUs — covering hipify, manual fixups, CMake changes, and OpenGL interop.
Tags: gpu, cuda, rocm, hip, c++, artificial life

24 Apr 2026
Mauri de Souza Meneguzzo
https://github.com/mauri870

## What is ALIEN?

**A**rtificial **LI**fe **EN**vironment.

A 2D particle physics simulation where digital organisms evolve, replicate, and compete.

- Soft bodies and fluids via a specialized particle engine
- Organisms are particle networks upgraded with sensors, muscles, neural nets
- Genomes encode body plans; offspring inherit and mutate them
- Simulations run with millions of particles in real time

The simulation kernel runs entirely on the GPU. Every particle update, collision, and cell-function evaluation happens in a CUDA (now HIP) kernel.

Winner of the ALIFE 2024 Virtual Creatures Competition.

